results.description: Edge Case 1: Perfect Puzzle - All students fit exactly with no gaps
Edge Case 2: One Minute Off - Each student's availability ends 1 minute before the next begins
Edge Case 3: Nested Availability - Students with completely nested time windows
Edge Case 4: Interleaved Windows - Complex overlapping pattern creating scheduling puzzle
Edge Case 5: Domino Effect - Scheduling one student blocks a chain of others
Edge Case 6: Musical Chairs - 8 students, 7 time slots at accessible locations
Edge Case 7: Location Hopping Required - Optimal solution requires frequent location switches
Edge Case 8: Isolated Islands - Students grouped by location with no overlap between groups
Edge Case 9: Mixed Duration Tetris - Multiple lesson durations that must fit perfectly
Edge Case 10: Prime Number Durations - Non-standard lesson durations that test granularity
Edge Case 11: Duration Mismatch - All students need 60 minutes but windows are 45 minutes
Edge Case 12: Swiss Cheese Schedule - Many small gaps in availability
Edge Case 13: Peak Hour Congestion - All students only available during prime time
Edge Case 14: Butterfly Effect - One student with strict availability affects entire schedule
Edge Case 15: Circular Dependency - Student A blocks B, B blocks C, C blocks A
Edge Case 16: Multiple Valid Solutions - Tests if algorithm finds optimal vs just feasible
Edge Case 17: Gap Minimization Trap - Minimizing gaps creates unsolvable situation
Edge Case 18: Greedy Trap - Scheduling shorter lessons first blocks longer ones
Edge Case 19: School Day Rush - 20 students all want after-school slots
Edge Case 20: Weekend Warriors - 12 students only available Saturday/Sunday
Edge Case 21: Lunch Break Puzzle - Teacher has lunch break creating scheduling gap
Edge Case 22: Resource Starvation - Some students consistently blocked by others
Edge Case 23: Minimum Viable Window - 15-minute window for 15-minute lesson
Edge Case 24: Time Zone Simulation - Students with availability offset by exact hours
Edge Case 25: Fairness vs Efficiency - Maximum students scheduled vs equal opportunity
